            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <div type="textpart" n="1" resp="MAC1945">
                <p> [The stone of] <foreign xml:lang="pgl">Canntianus</foreign> and of his father <foreign xml:lang="pgl">Maccutreni</foreign>. They lie here.</p>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" n="2" xml:lang="en" resp="MAC1945">
                    <p>No translation has been made beyond the suggestion that the inscription is a first name</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <list type="witDetail">
                    <item n="1">
                         <p>The Welsh Corpus notes that <q> CANNTIANI is the genitive of the name <hi rend="italic">Cantanius</hi>, which is attested on the Continent as a common name and as the name of a martyr of Aquileia praised by Venantius Fortunatus. It is presumably a Latin derivative...of the name <hi rend="italic">Cantius</hi>, ultimately from the Celtic name-element <hi rend="italic"> *kant-</hi>...The father's name, MACVTRENI, is Irish and recurs at Llywel (Pentre Poeth) 1 (B42), MAQITRENI / [M]ACCVTRENI</q>(Redknap and Lewis 2007, 235). The inscriptions could be referring to the same person but this is uncertain since the name was apparently popular in Britain and Ireland. The second element of the name may be related to Welsh <hi rend="italic">trwyn</hi> in the name <hi rend="italic">Cyndrwyn</hi> (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 235).</p>
                    </item>
                    <item n="2">
                        <p>The Welsh Corpus suggests that <q>the rendering of the ogam script appears to be schematic only, so that it may have corresponded to the Roman script</q>. Thus, it is uncertain what should be taken from the wide spacing of the characters on the drawing. It should be noted that Macalister read two further initial letters, BM, before the S in the inscription (CIIC:318) but these are not visible on the drawing (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 233-5; Macalister 1945).</p>
                    </item>
                </list>
                          </div>
